# PetCareApp - SwiftUI Development Rules

## Project Context
- Language: Swift 5.9+
- Framework: SwiftUI
- Minimum iOS: 16.0
- Architecture: MVVM
- State Management: @StateObject, @ObservableObject
- Persistence: UserDefaults (later CoreData)
- Notifications: UNUserNotificationCenter

## Code Style Guidelines
1. Use meaningful variable names (no abbreviations unless standard)
2. Follow Swift naming conventions (camelCase for variables, PascalCase for types)
3. Use explicit types for public APIs
4. Prefer structs over classes when possible
5. Use extensions for organizing code
6. Add // MARK: comments for sections
7. Always handle optionals safely (guard let, if let)
8. Use SwiftUI property wrappers correctly (@State, @Binding, @ObservedObject)

## File Structure Rules
- One type per file (except for small enums/structs)
- Group related files in folders
- Use Extensions/ folder for extension files
- Keep ViewModels separate from Views

## SwiftUI Best Practices
- Extract subviews when body gets complex (>20 lines)
- Use @ViewBuilder for conditional views
- Prefer built-in modifiers over custom views when possible
- Use .task {} instead of .onAppear for async work
- Use Spacer() instead of padding when appropriate

## Specific Instructions
- Always import Foundation and SwiftUI at top
- Use SF Symbols for icons (Image(systemName:))
- Implement accessibility labels
- Add preview provider for all views
- Use Identifiable protocol for list items
- Handle errors gracefully with Result type